    "Chang Kuo-Wei is the chairman of Starlux Airlines, Taiwan's newest international carrier.",
    "He is the youngest son of Chang Yung Fa, the late founder of Evergreen Marine, one of the world's largest shipping companies.",
    "Former chairman of the family's EVA Airways, Kuo-Wei was ousted from family businesses by his three half-brothers following Yung Fa's death in 2016.",
    "He struck out on his own and set up Starlux two years later, which went public on the Taiwan Stock Exchange in October 2024.",
    "The Taiwan Supreme Court ruled in August 2024 in favor of Kuo-Wei, confirming the validity of Yung Fung's will that leaves Kuo-Wei the bulk of his wealth."
